dct_title_s: South America, Argentina, Bahía Blanca (Raster Image)
dct_description_sm: Prepared and published by the Defense Mapping Agency Hydrographic/Topographic Center. Depths shown by isolines and soundings. "From Argentine charts to 1984." "Copyright 1995 by the United States Government. No copyright claimed under Title 17 U.S.C." "Soundings in meters." Includes source diagram and tidal information. Insets: Bahía Blanca, Puerto Belgrano and Puerto Rosales. Scale 1:15,000 -- Bahía Blanca, Puerto Ingeniero White to Puerto Galván. Scale 1:15,000. Map no.23122
This map is part of a collection of scanned and georeferenced nautical charts produced by the National Geospatial-Intelligence Agency (NGA).
This layer is presented in the WGS84 coordinate system for web display purposes. Downloadable data are provided in native coordinate system or projection.
